<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Common Dialogs]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=533&amp;p=2781#p2781"><![CDATA[
Every program can choose to use the new or the old style of common dialogs. I don't see a way to override that.<br /><br />BTW, I don't think 1366x768 is designed to work with 150% DPI. That reduces the effective resolution to 900x512. Even the very early versions of Windows required at least 800x600 resolution. Anything less than that you are asking for trouble.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=2">Ivo</a> — Tue Apr 16, 2013 8:53 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
